{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8a06f50-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s11"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11"},"text":"§ 11.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Foreign government defined","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “foreign government”, as used in this title except in sections 112, 878, 970, 1116, and 1201, includes any government, faction, or body of insurgents within a country with which the United States is at peace, irrespective of recognition by the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8a06f51-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 645","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/686"},"text":"62 Stat. 686","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/467/s11"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–467, § 11","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-08"},"text":"Oct. 8, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2001"},"text":"90 Stat. 2001","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb8a06f52-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb8a06f53-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 18, U.S.C., 1940 ed., §§ 98, 288, 349; ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s235"},"text":"section 235 of title 22","children":[],"tail":" U.S.C., 1940 ed., Foreign Relations and Intercourse; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s41"},"text":"section 41 of title 50","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., War and National Defense ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1917-06-15/ch30"},"text":"June 15, 1917, ch. 30","children":[],"tail":", title VIII, § 4, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/40/226"},"text":"40 Stat. 226","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The definition of “foreign government” contained in this section, with minor changes in phraseology, is from section 4 of title VIII of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1917-06-15"},"text":"June 15, 1917","children":[],"tail":" (Ch. 30, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/40/217"},"text":"40 Stat. 217","children":[],"tail":", 226), known as the Espionage Act of 1917. This definition was incorporated in sections 98, 288, and 349 of title 18 and in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s235"},"text":"section 235 of title 22","children":[],"tail":", Foreign Relations and Intercourse, and in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s41"},"text":"section 41 of Title 50","children":[],"tail":", War and National Defense, U.S.C., all in 1940 ed., since the definition was specifically enacted with reference to said sections and others not material here."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The remaining provisions of said sections 98 and 349 of title 18, U.S.C., 1940 ed., which were derived from sources other than said ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1917-06-15/tVIII/s4"},"text":"section 4 of title VIII of the act of June 15, 1917","children":[],"tail":", are incorporated in sections 502 and 957 of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8a06f54-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb8a06f55-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1976—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/467"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–467","children":[],"tail":" inserted “except in sections 112, 878, 970, 1116, and 1201” after “title”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
